{\*\pnseclvl1\pnucrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl2\pnucltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl3\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl4\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl5
\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl6\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl7\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl8\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang
{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl9\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}\pard\plain \s1\qc \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\b\fs32\lang2057\langfe1033\kerning32\langnp2057 Pipeline Component Context
\par }\pard \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\fs32\lang2057\langfe1033\kerning32\langnp2057 Requirements
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Overview
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \tab 
\par \tab 
Currently the only run time input to a server framework pipeline component is the data from the client or, if it is not the first component in the pipeline, the output from the previous component. However, the e-Diary project has requirements that it woul
d
 be easier to fulfil if they could access environmental request specific information such as the service and method name. Also, they would like to be able to add their own data to the environment and access it later on from a different component within th
e same pipeline.
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Requirements List
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1.\tab}}\pard\plain \ql \fi-360\li720\ri0\nowidctlpar\jclisttab\tx720\faauto\ls2\rin0\lin720\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 To make it possible to access environmental request specific information from within pipeline components.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2.\tab}To provide a mechanism by which individual custom components can add values to the environment and which are a
vailable to components appearing later in the same pipeline. The lifetime of these values is a single request.
\par }\pard \ql \li360\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs32\lang2057\langfe1033\kerning32\langnp2057 Design
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard\plain \s15\ql \fi720\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\f0 
A standard approach to this sort of problem is to provide a context. This stores various pieces of data related to the current service request. This would seem to be adequate to meet the requirements.
\par The service and method name will always be valid and available, will be set upon the context by the component container and cannot be changed by a component. Any piece of data that has these properties can be regarded as a }{\i\f0 system}{\f0 
 item. In order to provide the required extension mechanism }{\i\f0 user}{\f0  context items will be allowed. These can be set and fetched within a component.
\par An interface will be written called \'93IComponentContext\'94 with the following self-explanatory methods:
\par 
\par }{\i\f0 public Object getSystemItem(String key);
\par 
\par public Object getUserItem(String key);
\par public void putUserItem(String key, Object item);
\par public void removeUserItem(String key);
\par }{\f0 
\par }\pard \s15\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0 The suggested way to implement this is as a wrapper upo
n 2 maps: one for system items, one for user items. The implementation will make it possible to set system items but it is the above interface that will be passed to components. The reason system items are available via a generic method rather than specif
ic ones (for example, getMethodName) is that it allows new values to be added without changing the interface.
\par }\pard \s15\ql \fi720\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0 
\par The context could be made available to components by adding a parameter to the IComponent \'93process\'94 method but that would require all current impl
ementations, including those written by project teams, to be updated to reflect the interface change. In order to avoid this rework it will be expressed as a new method of IComponent called \'93setContext\'94. This will be implemented by the current \'93
AbstractComponent\'94 class (from which all other components inherit). This will mean zero rework for current implementations.
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par \tab It may also prove useful to have the context available from other places, namely from the custom code developers can write which plugs into predefined pipeline components:
\par 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1)\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-273\li993\ri0\nowidctlpar\jclisttab\tx993\faauto\ls3\rin0\lin993\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Java can be plugged in using the \'93Java\'94
 component. The developer implements ICustomProcessor. A \'93setContext\'94 method will be added to the interface. However, there is currently no abstract implementation of
 the interface that will allow this change to be made without effecting current implementations. Therefore an abstract layer will be added from which current implementations will have to inherit. This has the advantage of making it more likely that future
 interface changes will not require changes to existing implementations.
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2)\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-284\li993\ri0\nowidctlpar\jclisttab\tx993\faauto\ls3\rin0\lin993\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Javascript can be plugged in using the \'93
Script\'94 component. The developer writes a normal Javascript file but can access certain special \'93context\'94 items, made available via Apache R
hino. Therefore the new context will be added to the Javascript context. It will be available via a Javascript variable called \'93context\'94.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Provided System Items
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par \tab The following system items will be available:
\par 
\par 
